## Database Operations
- always backup data before destructive operations
- use transactions for multi-step database operations
- validate SQL queries before execution
- prefer parameterized queries to prevent SQL injection

## Test-Driven Development (TDD)
- write tests before implementing functionality (Red-Green-Refactor cycle)
- aim for high test coverage but focus on meaningful tests
- write unit tests for individual components
- create integration tests for component interactions
- use descriptive test names that explain the expected behavior
- keep tests simple, focused, and independent